<div type="translation">
<head>Translation</head>
<p> The fatherland <supplied reason="subaudible">set up a statue of</supplied> Tiberius Claudius Kapitoleinos son of Tiberius Claudius Smaragdos.</p>
</div>
<div type="commentary">
<head>Commentary</head>
<p>The only other Smaragdos attested so far is P. Aelius Claudius Smaragdos, <xref type="inscription" n="1353" href="020308">2.308</xref> (=67.554).</p><p>Ti. Cl. Kapitoleinos may very well be the very epimelete of two statues of Cl. Antonia Tatiana, <xref type="inscription" n="1793" href="120323">12.323</xref>, (=LBW 1597), <xref type="inscription" n="1723" href="020013">2.13</xref> (= 64.427), and the father of Ti. Aur. Cl. Ktesias, honoured in an inscription which might be the pair of this one <xref type="inscription" n="1794" href="120324">12.324</xref> =(LBW 1598).</p>
</div>
